---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const pageTitle = "Juana Aguilar Galang Scholarship Foundation";
---

<BaseLayout pageTitle={pageTitle}>
	<p><i>Empowering Dreams Through Education</i></p>

	<div>
		<h2>Our Mission</h2>
		<p>
			The Juana Aguilar Galang Scholarship Foundation is based upon the conviction that
			higher education is a right and not a privilege. The Foundation believes that
			education is essential to a healthy, functioning, and equitable society. It is for
			these reasons that the foundation aims to provide access to postsecondary education
			to members of our community who otherwise would not have the financial means to
			achieve their educational goals.
		</p>
	</div>

	<div>
		<h2>Our Vision</h2>
		<p>
			The Juana Aguilar Galang Scholarship Foundation sees higher education as an agent of
			change for individuals, families, and communities. We envision a society where
			underprivileged and marginalized youth - demonstrating resilience, steadfast ambition,
			and making the most of their God-given ability - achieve their life's goals and become
			productive citizens who will serve others in their community.
		</p>
	</div>

	<div>
		<h2>Our Objective</h2>
		<p>
			The Foundation awards scholarships to college students based on demonstrated academic
			achievement, financial need, excellent personal character, and active involvement in
			community service.
		</p>
		<p>
			The Foundation aims to actively mentor current scholars and alumni to ensure both
			college and post-college persistence and success. The Foundation believes we have a
			critical role to play in guiding our scholars through the challenging times, and
			providing support to their education beyond monetary assistance.
		</p>
	</div>

	<div>
		<h2>What We Provide</h2>
		
		<div>
			<h3>Financial Support</h3>
			<p>
				Scholars receive Php 18,000 per semester, distributed in biweekly payments. This
				support helps cover daily living expenses such as transportation, meals, school
				supplies, and other essential needs so students can focus fully on their education.
			</p>
		</div>

		<div>
			<h3>Mentorship & Guidance</h3>
			<p>
				We pair scholars with dedicated mentors who provide academic guidance, career advice,
				internship support, and regular check-ins throughout the school year.
			</p>
		</div>

		<div>
			<h3>Leadership & Community Service</h3>
			<p>
				Our scholars commit to school/community service each semester, developing strong
				character, responsibility, and a heart for serving others.
			</p>
		</div>

		<div>
			<h3>Long-Term Commitment</h3>
			<p>
				We support our scholars beyond financial aid - walking alongside them through college
				and preparing them for meaningful careers and community impact.
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</BaseLayout>